[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glenariff: Sheep farmer's fears after landslide

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A sheep farmer whose grazing land in the Glens of Antrim has been partly destroyed by a landslide has said it could be months before he is able to clear the debris.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
6 January 2016 Last updated at 18:56 GMT
Dermot McDonnell said he believes 23 of his flock are buried underneath and with more rain forecast he is worried tonnes of rock and soil could slip further onto the public road and property below.
Helen Jones reports.
